cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on sarcasm detection. Additionally, the use of a deep neural network with dense connectivity suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are also relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The use of convolutional layers in the network architecture also suggests a possible connection to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. Finally, the use of a case study to support the results suggests a possible connection to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
